{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Requesting salary history to be made unlawful in the UK.",
        "additional_details": "- A number of people are underpaid in the UK. Salary history should not be a factor in determining new pay as that undervalues the current market price for the position and skills of the employee.\r\n\r\n- There is gender pay gap in the UK, and this will help bridge closing the gap. This is a well known issue in the UK which the government is tackling.\r\n\r\n- Jobs will be offered based on skills, merit and demands of the job. Not gender, race or ethnicity.",
        "background": "Requesting salary history  as part of job selection process has to be made unlawful in the UK.This has been made a law in New York and other US states. So why not in the UK?\r\n\r\nBeing underpaid once shouldn't condemn you to a lifetime of inequality.",
